comments.body:
@twowTurtReynolds Here ya go:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vwiZXRNwW3M

This was a deliberate reproduction - I am spamming movement after Tail Lash ends, and it will let me cast spells, but it takes a few more seconds to be allowed to move again. If Nef had not been moved, I probably would have been chained into another Tail Lash, pretty much impossible to escape in this form.

@twowTurtReynolds I'm highly doubtful this isn't a bug. Normally Improved Shadow Bolt is not consumed by periodic damage nor by the application of such spells. I don't have testing proof but I don't think its unrealistic to assume Blizzard made stormstrike work the same way.

Another info for you, dots do not snapshot with "increase damage taken" debuffs on the enemy. If deadly poison or this new poison trinket consumes all of stormstrike charges when it gets applied, its ticks won't benefit from the 20% increased damage of stormstrike.

"so the street goes both ways here." seems like it only goes one way to me. If we use Improved Shadow Bolt talent as basis on how stormstrike should work, the application of periodic damage abilities should not consume a charge.

I've got the same problem today

@BinarySoup Did you manage to complete it?

upd: I've just completed it. The bug is not permanent, good luck :)

